abstract: Mr. Bloomberg has been an outspoken voice on gun control and climate change, but his views on taxes would put him on the conservative end of the Democratic field.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg has been an outspoken voice on gun control and climate change, but his views on taxes would put him on the conservative end of the Democratic field.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York and a billionaire, is likely to enter the Democratic presidential primary. Hereâ€™s a look at where he stands on some of the major issues in the race.

headline_main: Where Michael Bloomberg Stands on the Issues

abstract: A Bloomberg-Trump contest would be one between a maker and a faker.
snippet: A Bloomberg-Trump contest would be one between a maker and a faker.
lead_paragraph: Mike Bloomberg should run for president, for two reasons that ought to be dispositive. First, he would be a very good president, potentially a great one. Second, he stands a much better chance of beating Donald Trump than anyone in the current Democratic field.

headline_main: Should Mike Bloomberg Enter the Democratic Race?

abstract: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
snippet: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg disrupted the Democratic presidential field on Friday as he took his first steps into the 2020 race, unnerving supporters of Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and prompting Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders to accuse Mr. Bloomberg of seeking to buy the presidency.

abstract: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg is actively preparing to enter the Democratic presidential primary and is expected to file paperwork this week designating himself as a candidate in at least one state with an early filing deadline, people briefed on Mr. Bloombergâ€™s plans said.
